==Hong Kong Disneyland== Like the newer generations of the American Tomorrowlands, Hong Kong's version features an emphasis on metallic trim, with lots of blue and purple hues. Currently under construction outside the berm to the south of [[Autopia]] is [[Iron Man Experience]], the first Disney attraction to be based on a Marvel property, featuring [[Tony Stark]] recruiting guests to fend off [[Extraterrestrial life|extraterrestrial]] beings from attacking [[Hong Kong]].<ref name=THR>{{cite news|last=Chu|first=Karen|title=Hong Kong Disneyland to Open 'Iron Man' Experience in 2016|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/hong-kong-disneyland-open-iron-644562|accessdate=8 October 2013|newspaper=The Hollywood Reporter|date=8 October 2013}}</ref> In August 2014, UFO Zone was suspended in preparation for "Tomorrowland Party Zone", a stage as part of "Disney's Haunted Halloween" event during the expansion of "Iron Man Experience".
As part of "Star Wars: Tomorrowland Takeover" event since June 2016, the first three expansion attractions were all closed.<ref>{{cite news|title=Star Wars takes over Hong Kong Disneyland this summer|url=https://www.silverkris.com/stories/star-wars-takes-over-hong-kong-disneyland-summer}}</ref> In April 5, UFO Zone has been closed in preparation for [[Jedi Training: Trials of the Temple]] that premiered in June 25.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hong Kong Disneyland Reports Second-highest Revenues, Third-highest Attendance and Record Guest Spending|url=http://news-en.hongkongdisneyland.com/PressReleases/PressReleaseDetail.aspx?AssetId=42612a78-06ac-430f-8f5d-eca91af0ece2}}</ref> In May 2, [[Stitch Encounter]] was closed and re-themed to "Star Wars: Command Post". In June 11, when the event started, Autopia was closed.
In October 22, 2016, a new shop named "Expo Shop" was opened, it is between "Jedi Training: Trials of the Temple" and "Buzz Lightyear Astro Blasters".<ref>{{cite news|title=BREAKING: Opening Date Set for Iron Man Experience, First-Look Inside the Amazing Queue & More|url=http://wdwnt.com/blog/2016/11/breaking-opening-date-set-iron-man-experience-first-look-inside-amazing-queue/}}</ref> The land will close in 2023 to make way for the new Marvel land.
